parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat back recline mechanism can cause the seat to suddenly recline or collapse, which can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The seat back reclines or collapses suddenly
the seat back falls backward while driving
the seat is stuck in a reclined position
the seat is difficult to adjust or return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can delay or prevent the correction of safety issues, leaving vehicles in an unsafe condition and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealership reports no parts available to correct the recall issue
long wait times for parts
inability to schedule repair due to parts unavailability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of the caster camber kit can cause improper wheel alignment, leading to uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle requires a caster camber kit to achieve proper wheel alignment
manufacturer failed to install the kit
improper wheel alignment
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose or Missing Upper A-Arm Bolts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or missing upper A-arm bolts can cause the suspension system to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Upper A-arm bolts came loose or fell off
unusual noises or vibrations from the suspension
reduced vehicle stability
loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the brakes lock up
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle's electronic stability control system malfunctions.
